<h2>Adjudicator</h2>

<p>The Adjudicator is a village-aligned role. Every night they can examine a player to determine whether they are capable of killing or not.</p>

<h3>Role Type</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Alignment: Village</li>
  <li>Viewed Alignment: Village</li>
  <li>Seen visiting: Yes</li>
  <li>User of witchcraft: No</li>
  <li>Killer: No</li>
  <li>Kill type: N.A.</li>
  <li>Night immunity: No</li> 
 </ul>

<h3>Notes</h3>
<ul>
    <li>You cannot distinguish between village-aligned killers (e.g. Huntsman) or evil (e.g. Vampires or Witches).</li>
    <li>All werewolves, even those that do not actively kill, such as Bloodhounds, are considered killers.</li>
    <li>The roles you will see as killers are: All wolves, Huntsman, Maple Wolf, Militia, Witch Hunter, Zealot, Furie, Warlock, Witch, Familiar Militia, Vampire, Vampire Master, Necromancer, and Voodoo Doctor.</li>
</ul>

